# 1. Introduction

Customer support is one of the most important business functions in modern eCommerce platforms. Every day, organizations receive thousands of customer requests related to order tracking, refunds, cancellations, product recommendations, account management, and general inquiries.

Handling these requests manually increases operational costs, response times, and workload on support teams.

To address these challenges, this Proof of Concept (POC) demonstrates an AI-powered Customer Support Automation System that utilizes multiple AI agents to understand customer intent and generate intelligent responses using Large Language Models (LLMs).

The solution is built using FastAPI as the backend framework, CrewAI for multi-agent orchestration, Groq for cloud-based AI inference, and Ollama as a local fallback model, providing a scalable and reliable architecture.



# 2. Project Objective

The primary objectives of this prototype are:

- Automate repetitive customer support interactions.
- Reduce response time for customer queries.
- Demonstrate a multi-agent AI architecture.
- Provide intelligent product recommendations.
- Improve customer experience using AI-generated responses.
- Support multiple LLM providers for increased reliability.
- Build a modular system that can be easily extended for production deployment.



# 3. Problem Statement

Traditional customer support systems face several operational challenges:

- High operational costs due to human dependency.
- Long waiting times during peak business hours.
- Repetitive handling of common customer requests.
- Limited scalability with increasing customer volume.
- Difficulty providing 24×7 customer assistance.

An AI-powered customer support automation system can instantly resolve frequently asked questions, assist customers with order-related issues, and recommend products while significantly reducing manual effort and improving service quality.


# 4. Solution Overview

The proposed solution is an AI-powered Customer Support Automation System designed to automate common customer interactions in an eCommerce environment. The system follows a modular multi-agent architecture where each AI agent is responsible for handling a specific category of customer requests.

Instead of using a single monolithic chatbot, the application divides responsibilities among specialized agents:

- Query Agent – Handles general customer support questions and FAQs.
- Order Agent – Processes order-related requests such as tracking, cancellation, and refunds.
- Recommendation Agent – Provides AI-powered product recommendations based on customer queries.

A centralized LLM Service acts as the communication layer between the agents and the underlying language models. The service first attempts to generate responses using Groq's cloud-based LLM and automatically switches to Ollama when the cloud service is unavailable.

This architecture improves modularity, maintainability, scalability, and system reliability while providing an enhanced customer experience.



