## Architecture Description

The customer interacts with the chatbot through a web-based interface developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

The frontend sends customer requests to the FastAPI backend through REST APIs.

The backend performs intent detection and routes the request to the appropriate AI agent.

Each agent communicates with the centralized LLM Service instead of directly interacting with an AI model.

The LLM Service first attempts to generate a response using Groq's cloud-hosted language model. If the cloud service is unavailable or encounters an error, the request is automatically redirected to the locally hosted Ollama model.

The generated response is returned to the FastAPI backend and finally displayed to the customer through the chatbot interface.



